# Python

- Follow PEP 8. Use type hints on public functions.
- Prefer Pythonic idioms (comprehensions, context managers, dataclasses).
- Validate external data with schema-based validation (e.g. pydantic).
- Tests with pytest: fixtures, parametrization, mocking; target 80%+ coverage.
- Handle exceptions explicitly; never bare `except:`.
